Title: Using Natural Language for Database Design  
Author: Edith Buchholz and Antje Dsterhft 
Address: Rostock, A.-Einstein-Str.21 18059 Rostock, Germany  
Affiliation: Department of Computer Science University of  
Abstract: This paper deals with a natural language dialogue tool for supporting the database design pr ocess. We want to illustrate how natural language (German) can be used for obtaining a skeleton design and for supporting the acquisition of semantics of the prospective database. The approach is based on the assumption that verbs form a central part in defining the meaning of sentences and imply semantic roles in the sentences which have to be filled by objects. We are using a moderated dialogue for drawing the designer's attention to these objects in order to extract comprehensive information about the domain. 
